I give a vague answer that could be interpreted

\n<Udo Takeru>The food is pretty good, huh? I prepared the best
for this day, you know♪
\n<Minato Neon>Well... it's delicious...

\n<\N[5]>\FF[61]\F[\V[4]]\AA[FF] So... Udo-san, could you
tell us soon?

\N[5]-san urged Director Udo to talk. Perhaps
they sensed something from my response and were
considerate of me.

\n<Udo Takeru>\FF[61]\F[\V[4]]\AA[F] Tch... Premature
ejaculators don't get any girls, huh?

\n<Udo Takeru>Hmph, well... fine. Then let's start with the
details about this mansion.
And finally... Udo began to talk about work.

\n<Udo Takeru>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[F] ...Well, that's about
it. Neon-chan, do you have any questions?
\n<Minato Neon>Um, well...

\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[FF]I once... organized the
information I received from Director Udo in my
head. Among that information, there were
surprising facts.

First of all, it seems that this mansion was
inherited as a legacy from Director Udo's
grandfather. And that grandfather is none other
than the world-famous director, Udo Isao, who is
said to be a great director of the Showa era. I
was surprised by this fact.

Some of the works he left behind in the world,
even someone like me who is musically inclined but
knows nothing about movies, knew. It seems that
the film Director Udo Takeru is making this time
is an homage to one of those works.

\n<Minato Neon>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Regarding the character
I will be playing...

\n<Udo Takeru>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[F] Ah... You must have been
surprised, right? The moment I saw Neon-chan on
TV, I felt something like a fateful connection.

From the moment the script arrived, I read it over
and over again. The character I will be playing,
Reiko, is incredibly similar to me in terms of
appearance, personality, and even the way she
speaks. Well... except for one thing...

\n<Udo Takeru>So, Neon-chan, I want you to strive to get as
close as possible to the character named Reiko
during this training camp.

\n<Udo Takeru>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[F] First of all... let's
stop speaking like that from now on. It's not that
we're being disrespectful, but it's part of
getting into character, you know?

\n<Minato Neon>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[FF] Yes... no... ah, I
understand.

I was actually confused when they forced me to
speak in a more natural way, rather than focusing
on my character. But... I felt hesitant about
acting childish, so I managed to put on a fake
smile and respond somehow.

\n<Udo Takeru>If there's anything you don't understand, feel
free to rely on me, okay? After all, I'm here as
both your acting coach and director, you know?
\n<Udo Takeru>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[F] Well then...

\n<Udo Takeru>\FF[\V[2]]\F[\V[4]]\AA[F] Oh, and as for meals,
